# Media Calls

## Connect with video and/or audio
```javascript
await ZYNQ.peer.connect('peer-id', {
  video: true,
  audio: true,
  resolution: 720,
  fps: 30
})
```

## Handling streams
```javascript
// Your own camera preview
ZYNQ.peer.on('local-stream', stream => {
  localVideo.srcObject = stream
})

// Video/audio from the other peer
ZYNQ.peer.on('remote-stream', ({ peerId, stream }) => {
  remoteVideo.srcObject = stream
})
```

The library automatically answers incoming calls when you call `accept()` and manages the local stream (reuses it and stops the camera when no peers remain).
